The paper deals with the Delaunay triangulation of point sets, which is a fundamental topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The complexity analysis of the Delaunay triangulation involves the study of the geometric properties of the point set, such as spread and density, which are also relevant in other areas of computer science, such as data structures (cs.DS), graphics (cs.GR), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and control theory (cs.SY). Therefore, these sub-categories are likely to be relevant to the paper.
